caption: Loveeeessss it here. My friend and I new favorite spot. Our waitress was very nice and the food was delicious. Definitely will be coming back. Especially for Happy Hour.
Good food, good service. Nice outdoor shed with heaters and also spacious seating on the sidewalk. Fresh tacos and great corn soup!
Probably have eaten here over 30 times since I moved to the area.  Everything about this restaurant is what you’re looking for.  Great people/service, great food, and great drinks!

Came for the cocktails which were excellent! Got some small noms and they were delicious. Would definitely come again for more cocktails a more substantial meal.  There is outdoor seating and a fun atmosphere.

Saw this cute spot and had to come in. Food was great, drinks, and staff were great and friendly. Lots of outdoor space. Queso fundido was a good move. Only reason I gave 4 stars instead of 5 is because they have a 10% Covid surcharge... (it’s separate from gratuity)...
The Eggs Benedict brunch item was phenomenal. The chorizo was delicious and the drinks are strong. I would go here for brunch every week if I could.
Very good food and service
Outstanding food and deserts, wonderful owners and staff.Took time to check on us and very accommodating. My favorite new spot on the Upper West Side
Love this place!! Best fish tacos. Order from here at least once a week and it's always amazing
Great little neighborhood place, delicious carnitas and tacos, great brunch.
Good Food Nice People

The delivery is amazing, the guacamole is awesome and the waiters are so nice. They also gave us free tater tots. This is the best Mexican restaurant in the world. I got delivery from The Calaveras 3 days in a row. That’s how awesome it is. They arrive always on time. I really recommend The Calaveras.
Margarita and Cold Carajillo were out of this world! Ceviche was fresh and delicious. Can't wait for my Carne Asada and tacos! Edit: those were amazing as well. I wish I had 2 stomachs
Came by earlier today and the staff was super friendly and the service was quick. I got the Coliflor rostizada and the guacamole and chips. Definitely coming back again.
My friend brought me something from here... ehhhh probably couldn’t have been any better than it wasn’t. Coffee could be made better.

This place is a gem! The food is exceptional—and such great value. Guacamole was balanced, chips cooked and salted to perfection, fish tacos melted in your mouth. Can’t wait to order again and explore the rest of the menu
We ordered delivery, absolutely amazing! Absolutely great tacos al pastor, and fair price too!
The Calaveras is open for pickup and delivery, and the food (and drink!) is just as great as ever. Try The One from Oaxaca. You will thank me later. So delicious.
If you're looking for quality Mexican food in this neighborhood, The Calaveras really does it! Food is delicious and the staff is welcoming!

This is the message I posted to my Facebook page five minutes ago:  I just had an amazing meal that was delivered from The Calaveras, located at 949 Columbus Ave on the Upper West Side of NYC--Amazing food! There was even a lovely message written on top of the container that housed my homemade tater tots that came with the roasted corn soup--"Thank you for keeping us going, Gloria!" I also had the small order of   Tacos Arrachera (grilled skirt steak tacos).  I feel so blessed and cared for by these people--amazing!.  The food was incredible.  Safety first!  Be well everyone.  G-out!
Great  traditional mexican food and  great drinks (mezcal cocktails) the calaveras is the best place¡  Víctor and Natalia  they awesome people¡

Good/Decent food  . . . Quite narrow spiral staircase leads you into ample dining space  . . . Patio area for the Spring/Summer  . . . Courteous staff  .   . . Erotic/Exotic drinks  . . . Moderately priced
Amazing service and tasty traditional Mexican food located in a romantic space. Perfect date spot.

One of the best mexican restaurants in NYC. I know that we can find more and more mexican food options in this great city but to find a really authentic and delicious food it's a challenge. Well, that said please visit The Calaveras and don't think that the place is just what you can see from the street, there are more space downstairs as you can see from the pictures and the chilaquiles with steak are woooooow 😋😋
Came here for a birthday and they were very accommodating and we loved the wine cellar vibe downstairs, good service and yummy food

What a great restaurant. The food was delicious— flavorful but also healthy, my salmon was perfectly prepared. Indeed family friendly but still bustling and enjoyable if we didn’t have kids there. The margarita hit the spot. We’ll be back!
Have ordered delivery a few times now. The food is amazing, hot and arrives pretty quickly. Probably our favorite Mexican food spot in the UWS/Harlem area.
Downstairs

Some dishes where great, some so-so. I think some of the food was overpriced for small portions. For example 9$ for 4 strawberries. Or 18$ for a small enchilada as a main course. The atmosphere was nice and service was good.
One of the best places to eat, drink and have good time. Did not want to share my little haven but... the staff is so nice and the chefs have outdone themselves! It is a "must visit" on the UWS.
Great Mexican restaurant with good drinks and nice service. I can recommend the vegetarian Empanadas and Hibiscus Margarita.

Great waitress, awesome Ambiance, and food is delicious. What more can you want? It looks small from street level but when you go downstairs you have a spacious yet cozy space. Guacamole was delicious. Will be back

Met up with some friends for dinner but decided to leave after appetizers.  Margaritas - very good White sangria - tasted like syrup Mexican cider - very good. A steal for $4 Chicken tacos - crispy shell..dry Shrimp empanadas - hard and may have had one piece of shrimp chopped up into smaller pieces Elote - I didn’t try this but my companions didn’t finish it  Service was ok. The bartender was warm and informative. The waitress was aloof.  As most have noted, the restaurant is small and located downstairs. I did not like that there was no one upstairs manning what appeared to be the take out area where the entryway is. Be mindful that at night, this is not the safest especially when there is a restroom upstairs and the door is unlocked. Anyone could walk in and the diners downstairs would have no warning.  The fare here appears to cater to the area. If you’re seeking good, authentic Mexican - this is not it.
Very good food!!
Great service excellent Coffee
Calaveras Cafe is now open at 947 Columbus Avenue (106th-107th).
Awesome food and drinks.. Bartender makes a mean margarita. Definitely my new go to spot in the neighborhood.

This place is perfect! The food is fresh and flavourful, the ambience lifted my spirits, and the service is super friendly. Can’t wait to be back again and again!  I eat ceviche every week and never had one like this before! A must try! :)
Great Mexican place with lots of choice and really delicious tacos 😋🌮

Beyond five stars. I did not want to call the restaurant –again –to tell them how amazing the food is -so I’ll write a review. Every single time I order via Grubhub it is quick and extremely delicious. There’s obviously some serious culinary art going on -Mexican food at it’s finest! 🇲🇽
Great place, good food and wonderful staff.

Unbelievable is an understatement. Went for lunch. The sangria is delicious and the Mexican coffee is superb! Cheese Enchiladas de mole are a must! Do not skimp on dessert as the both the flan and churros are perfection. No Mexican place is complete without chips and salsa and these were amazing. You will walk away happy wondering what just hit you!

Guys. Guys. People who live in this neighborhood. Please don't let this place go out of business. It's so f-ing good. The fish tacos and quesadilla huitlacoche are both on another planet. Can we please make this place a thing. It deserves it.
Beautiful place,  good service.  Drinks ok.
Awesome food and vibe
Great good 👍🏻👌🏻

A charming small space with delicious food. I love their corn soup, steak tacos, and authentic offerenda.  Everything we ate was delicious. When ordering tacos for sure get three instead of two.. they’re small but SUPER QUALITY. The corn soup was even better than i would have imagined. This place was a little pricey for our typically low low budget but it was worth it!
Small bar on top but big downstairs @1st look the food seems as if it wont be enough but the flavor makes up for everything & great service too!!
Great spot to get something when in a rush. The customer service is prompt, prices are fair, great atmosphere. I highly recommend this spot.
Excellent.  Best Mexican in the neighborhood.  Good margaritas too.
Great dishes, fun cocktails, and really nice staff. The tacos, mole enchiladas, and ceviche were fantastic. Horchata cocktail super tasty!

Shared 2 dishes, a suiza and s mole, and both were wonderful.  The chips, salsa and guac were over and above that of which i normally have.  It is an hour, by subway, from where I reside. I will be back!
Carnitas tacos were great!
Great good. Great service. They had a delicious handmade tortilla wirh mushrooms too. The shrimp app is a meal in its own.
Great food and lovely atmosphere
Service great, nice place. Food was good but  small plates. Not a lot of food on the plate for the price but tasted really good
I hosted a surprise birthday party for my wife here. It was fun and they made it easy.  All the guests loved the restaurant and the margaritas.      I really like this place.
Genuine central Mexican food. Excellent drinks as well. Fantastic tortillas. An absolute find in a neighborhood that normally just does low-grade Mexican.
Amazing and super friendly staff. Food was stupendous.
Probably the best Tacos in NY. Great spot, do not be afraid by the cold entrance, downstairs is where the fun is!!!
Great hidden gem!  The enchilada suiza’s were delicious. Great downstairs bar.  Staff was excellent.  Will go back very soon!
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
Authentic!

A great experience - cool vibe, downstairs and up, delicious drink and foods. I loved their  Chips, esPecially the shApe. Also the salsas and guacamole and enchiladas were superb, as was the ceviche. Further, the staff and the owner were totally warm and welcoming. Can’t wait to go back.
Food was delish! Cocktails were perfectly made. We will come back!

Great Atmosphere. Delicious Mexican Cuisine. Great Decor. Staff is kind and friendly. Sopes are delicious when available (got them on Cinco de Mayo). Just be aware the entrance has an upstairs bar, but the full restaurant is down below... don't worry if the upstairs is empty... underneath it will be hoppin.
Great food I love this place great staff it is a true hidden gem
We ordered beef and fish taco, the fish taco is very well flavored and the steak was with large chunk of meat. We were impressed withe the quality of food.
(Translated by Google) Good food and Mexican music  (Original) Buena comida y musica mexicana

This restaurant is phenomenal. The atmosphere is lovely. The decor is beautiful. The staff is courteous and friendly. White sangria is absolutely delicious.  The shrimp and mashed potatoes is devine. The flavor is excellent. The sweet plantains with the salsa verde and cheese is an amazing combination of sweet and savory. I ate here visiting from Miami and I know good latin food and this was scrumptious.  I would totally go back!

Great place and fun small space. Not crowded, attentive staff, wonderful food and drinks. Not often do I find fresh and perfect guacamole without a lot of junk in it, fried zucchini blossoms (please make these as an appetizer all onto themselves...) and huitlacoche. Hibiscus mescal drink was to die for. Music was all over the place, and I liked that. We sat inside. I wish I could have done mix and match on the tacos - luckily my friend was on board with oreder-n-swap. Carnitas were excellent and pescado was good, my other friend loves her roasted chicken.
Honestly, really, HONESTLY, best Ceviche I have ever had.  Amazing!
Absolutely in LOVE with this place!! So happy we came across this delicious hidden gem ❤️

First of all... The fish tacos!  The decor is beautiful and the traditional clay plates they use really gives it an extra flare on the experience. Service was impeccable as well.  Guacamole is simple but the reality is that some restaurants get it wrong. The Calaveras Guac is amazing as well. Will definitely frequent this place.
Very nice quaint place. Has out back outside eating area. Good service

Nice cozy place. Has a small up stairs bar but the real place is downstairs. Feels warm and not like a basement.  Simply decorated and has a good looking bar. Small outdoor patio like space.  They are pretty new so things might change but the service was good and food is recommendable.
The carnitas tacos were very good. The service and the atmosphere were excellent.
This is now one of my favorite Mexican restaurants in town. The service and food are always excellent and the place itself is beautiful.
Marvelous Mexican, awesome ambience. Downstairs with patio and great natural light. Mexican twist im eggs Benedict (tamal and chorizo). Delicious drinks.

This place is so gorgeous. The street level entrance is cozy and modern but downstairs there’s a huuuge dining area space with an outdoor space when the weather is nice. The owners were around and very friendly, they recommended the zucchini empanadas which were so delicious I had to take some home. I will be sure to come back!
